&lt;p&gt;The Director, International Growth is a critical strategic leader responsible for defining and leading the NFL’s international growth agenda. This role owns the development and execution of the League’s global expansion strategy, combining&amp;nbsp;rigorous analytical thinking, structured problem-solving, and disciplined project leadership to shape the future of the NFL’s international business. As a senior thought partner to the Managing Director, International and the leadership team, the role drives high-impact initiatives that accelerate the League’s expansion and deepen its influence across global markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is responsible for developing&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;market entry strategies, long-term growth plans, and data-driven fan development models to guide decision-making across international territories. The Director will lead a team and coordinate across Clubs, international offices, and League stakeholders to translate complex market dynamics into clear strategic recommendations and executable plans, ensuring consistent and scalable growth of fandom and commercial value globally.&lt;/p&gt;
