&lt;p&gt;As a Business Relationship Manager/Director, you will be responsible for representing the IT department to the business for a portfolio of IT applications used throughout the organization.&amp;nbsp; This includes knowing the user base and understanding the issues facing the business department(s) who utilize IT’s product(s), creating/updating product management deliverables (support models, roadmaps, training strategy, product reviews), managing 2nd level application support, application training, product administration and 3rd party vendors that support the product(s). In addition, you will be responsible for project related tasks and/or deliverables for projects that impact the supported product(s).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires you to be able to communicate with all areas of the company and establish a strong relationship with stakeholders, vendors, and IT shared services to find innovative solutions that are aligned with the organization’s short-term and long-term objectives.&amp;nbsp; You will work with the business and IT to define application objectives, helping them understand the product positioning, key benefits, and target use cases of the application. You will also serve as the internal and external evangelist for your product offering, often working or embedding yourself with the business to better understand their true needs. You will manage the resolution of production support related issues and partner with Product stakeholders to ensure tickets are updated and issues are worked as quickly as possible. You will work with project management, business analysts and technical counterparts to define product release requirements. You will also serve as the liaison to your vendors, establishing a business relationship with their customer success, support, and product management teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This onsite contract engagement opportunity compensates at $3000 to $3800 weekly. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
