&lt;p&gt;The NFL is seeking an Integrated Sales Operations Coordinator to support media sales operations, including media-based sponsorships and sales development initiatives across NFL Media properties. This is a part-time (up to 29 hours per week) position supporting the execution of media sponsorships throughout the NFL Season.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support asset management for NFL O&amp;amp;O properties on NFL.com&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a record of sponsored links for NFL.com landing pages, editorials, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a database of sponsored product and content platform opportunities, which includes the status of working and sold business, start/end dates, and execution details for varying platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and manage inbound sales requests by touching base with content teams across NFL Digital Media&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the implementation of custom client creative for digital home page takeovers; provide quality assurance for sponsored campaigns before going live when possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with NFL Media colleagues and support the Integrated Sales and Monetization team using established processes to execute multi-platform sales deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support monitoring reporting for sponsored social campaigns and tracking engagement data for monetized social campaigns&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with NFL Network, digital, and social media content producers on the execution of sponsored content campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, update support and monitor reporting needs, as requested&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with implementation and execution of sponsored voting platforms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve all internal and external issues associated with ad campaigns, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the NFL ad serving vendor in the setup, development, and execution of changes related to site advertising footprints across digital, social, and mobile platforms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3+ years of interactive marketing, digital product development, campaign management, trafficking, or ad operations experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Key Attributes / Characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive thinker with strong organizational skills and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A problem solver who can make situational assessments and recommend actions to management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of and experience in a consumer-facing digital content space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A sports fan in general, and more specifically, an NFL fan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physical Demands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to meet basic physical demands in an office setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;0-5% (Limited travel; Potential to attempt local NFL games)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
